This paper is about revenue maximization in selling a single item to multiple buyers, which is a classic problem in game theory and mechanism design. The paper compares the revenue performance of four commonly used mechanisms and establishes tight revenue gaps among them. This topic falls under the subfield of algorithmic game theory and mechanism design, which is covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. cs.GT (Game Theory) is the most likely category, as it covers the theoretical foundations of game theory and mechanism design. cs.EC (Economics and Computation) is also a likely category, as it focuses on the intersection of computer science and economics, including mechanism design and auctions. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are less likely but still possible categories, as they both deal with algorithmic techniques for solving optimization problems. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the least likely category, as the paper does not involve any machine learning techniques.
